====== Tutorial 3 — Shell variables, text editors ======

===== Variables =====

  * Shell uses two types of variables 
    * **Local variables** - variables that are not exported to subprocesses
    * **Environment variables** - variables that are exported to subprocesses

===== Variables =====

  * Set a variable 
    * ''PAGER=less ; man man ; PAGER=less man man''
  * Display value stored in variable
    * ''echo $PAGER''
  * Display local / global variables
    * ''set ; env ; export -p''
  * Unset variable
    * ''unset PAGER''
  * Export variable
    * <code>export PAGER       
export PAGER=less  (except of sh)</code>

  * Permanent variable settings
    * Add the setting to the shell configuration file (e.g. ~/.profile or ~/.bash_profile).

