===== Aliasing =====

  * An alias is a shorthand notation to enable you to customize and abbreviate commands.
  * Aliases are not exported to subshells.
  * Setup an alias: ''alias ll='ls -l' ; alias la='ll -a' ''
  * Display all aliases: ''alias ; alias ll; type ll''
  * Unset alias: ''unalias ll''
  * Permanent alias settings
    *Add the setting to the shell configuration file (e.g. ~/.bashrc).

===== Text editors =====

  * ''joe'' \\ ASCII text screen editor, help ''^KH''
  * ''vi'' \\ ASCII text screen editor
  * ''gedit'' \\ graphical text screen editor
  * ''emacs'' \\ graphical/ASCII text screen editor

===== Prompt + =====

  * Variables PS1 and PS4
    * ''PS1''	primary prompt string
    * ''PS2''	secondary prompt (used in multi-linecommands)
    * ''PS3''	prompt string in ''select'' loop
    * ''PS4''	prompt string for execution trace (''set -x'')
  * Backslash-escaped  special  characters 

|  ''\d'' |…| the date  |
|  ''\t'' |…| the time (HH:MM:SS)  |
|  ''\A'' |…| the time (HH:MM)  |
|  ''\h'' |…| hostname |
|  ''\u'' |…| username  |
|  ''\w'' |…| working directory |

